President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring October 2016 as National Energy Action Month. The proclamation emphasizes the need to address energy challenges and promote clean and efficient energy production in order to ensure a sustainable future. The United States has made progress in reducing reliance on foreign oil and increasing fuel efficiency standards for vehicles. The country is also working with Canada and Mexico to pursue regional energy security and combat climate change. Efforts are being made to diversify the energy portfolio and increase access to cleaner forms of energy. The proclamation highlights the importance of achieving a low-carbon future and meeting emissions reduction goals. The United States is leading by example in reducing carbon pollution while striving for a cleaner environment and a stronger economy. The proclamation recognizes the need for continued work to achieve the clean energy economy of the future and encourages citizens to reduce their carbon footprint and energy consumption.